@page "/get-involved"

<section class="gi-hero">
    <h1>Get Involved</h1>
    <p>
        Ripple is built on community participation. Whether you’re a student, neighbor, educator, 
        or professional, there’s a place for you here. You can volunteer, learn, collaborate, or 
        help us grow our impact.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="gi-section">
    <h2>Ways to Get Involved</h2>

    <div class="gi-grid">
        <div class="gi-card">
            <h3>Volunteer with Ripple</h3>
            <p>
                Help with planting, harvesting, packaging, cleaning, and outreach. No prior experience 
                is required — we’ll teach you everything you need to know.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="gi-card">
            <h3>Community Garden & Personal Systems</h3>
            <p>
                Learn aquaponics hands‑on through small personal‑use systems and community garden units. 
                Great for families, students, and anyone curious about sustainable food.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="gi-card">
            <h3>Workshops & Tours</h3>
            <p>
                Join educational tours and workshops to learn how aquaponics works, why it matters, 
                and how it supports food security in Chicago.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="gi-card">
            <h3>Research & Collaboration</h3>
            <p>
                Students, educators, and researchers can partner with Ripple to study system design, 
                sustainability, biology, and community impact.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="gi-card">
            <h3>Support Our Work</h3>
            <p>
                If you can’t volunteer in person, you can still support Ripple through donations, 
                partnerships, or spreading the word.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="gi-section gi-cta">
    <h2>Ready to Get Involved?</h2>
    <p>
        Reach out, sign up for a shift, or connect with us about collaboration opportunities. 
        Together, we can grow something meaningful.
    </p>

    <div class="gi-buttons">
        <a href="/donate" class="btn donate">Donate</a>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn primary">Contact Us</a>
    </div>
</section>
